Virtual House Call for Parents and Families

Ask Pediatricians and School Medical Experts About COVID-19 and Back-to-School

Save-the-Date
The State Department of Education, together with health care providers, such as pediatricians and school medical experts, will host a virtual house call for parents and families to ask the medical experts about COVID-19 and safe strategies for back-to-school.

Date: Thursday, August 13, 2020
Time: 5:00 pm to 6:00 pm
Registration Link: https://ctserc.net/medadvisors813
Contact: Dr. Stephanie Knutson at Stephanie.knutson@ct.gov

Please share with families of school-age children.
Friday CAFE Website Friday CAFE Website
Other questions? For more information contact Judy Carson at judy.carson@ct.gov or 860-807-2122.
Sponsored by a collaboration of CSDE, CREC, SERC/PIRC and our Advisory Group.

post_text: Thanks to the Torrington Police Department for sharing in our love reading! City of Torrington Police Department
shared_text:
City of Torrington Police Department
February 12 at 12:16 PM ·

The Torrington Police Department would like to thank the Northwest Connecticut Chamber Education Foundation, Y Literacy Volunteers, and Forbes School for inviting us to take part in the 29th Read Aloud Day! Read Aloud Day provides an opportunity for our officers to interact with students through the joy of reading (and a little question and answer too). Officers Santiago, Abalan, and Yabrosky, as well as Sgt. Maiga had a great time and look forward to taking part in the event again in the future. @Northwest Connecticut Chamber of Commerce @Torrington Public Schools @Northwest CT YMCA @LitWorld @City of Torrington Police Department

-Lt. Johnson

Good afternoon. This is Susan Lubomski, Superintendent for Torrington Public Schools. The Secondary Budget Public Hearing scheduled for tonight is postponed to Monday, March 25th at 6:00PM in the THS Media Center. We will be addressing the secondary, curriculum, technology, facilities and athletics budgets that evening. The regular Budget Sub-committee meeting will be held on March 25th at 5:30PM. Thank you for your flexibility.

Buenas tardes. Soy Susan Lubomski, Superintendente de las Escuelas Publicas de Torrington. Vamos a posponer nuestra segunda reunión de audiencia pública de presupuesto de esta noche para el lunes, 25 de Marzo a las 6:00 pm en THS. Esa noche estaremos dirigiéndonos a los presupuestos para la secundaria, currículo, tecnología y deportes. La reunión del subcomité de presupuesto será el 25 de marzo a las 5:30pm. Gracias por su flexibilidad.

Good evening. This is Susan Lubomski, Superintendent for Torrington Public Schools. Due to the icy weather conditions, all schools, offices, and PDG and VOICES pre-k will have a two hour delay tomorrow, Wednesday, February 13th. The morning pre-k at East and THS are cancelled. We will continue to monitor the weather conditions in the morning as well in the event of any needed updates. Any necessary changes will be made by 7:00AM. Thank you.

Buenas noches. Es Susan Lubomski, Superintendente de las Escuelas Públicas de Torrington. Debido a las condiciones del clima helado, todas las escuelas, oficinas, pre-K PDG y VOICES, tendrán un retraso de dos horas mañana, Miércoles, 13 de Febrero. El Pre-K en la Escuela East y en la Escuela Superior estarán cancelados. Continuaremos monitoreando las condiciones climáticas en la mañana por si fuera necesario alguna actualización. Cualquier cambio necesario se realizara para las 7:00 am. Gracias.

post_text: Good Evening, Families, This is Assistant Superintendent, Susan Fergusson. Tomorrow, Friday Jan 25th, the Naugatuck Valley Railroad will be conducting tests on all railroad tracks in Torrington from 8:00am to 5:00pm. These tests include checking the working status of all lights, signals and gates. I am calling to let you know that this could potentially affect the timing of the buses to and from the schools. Thank you in advance for your understanding. Buenas Noches Familias, Es la Asistente de la Superintendente, Susan Fergusson. Mañana, Viernes, 25 de Enero, El Naugatuck Valley Railroad, llevara a cabo pruebas de las pistas del ferrocarril en Torrington de 8:00 am a 5:00 pm. Estas pruebas incluyen la comprobación del estado de todas las luces, señales y puertas. Los llamo para dejarles saber que esto podría afectar potencialmente el horario de los autobuses de la búsqueda y despido de los de los estudiantes. Gracias de antemano por su atención.

post_text:
The Connecticut Music Educators Association selected the Torrington HS Band to perform at the Connecticut Music Educators Association All-State Conference on Friday April 12, 2019 at the Hartford Convention Center. This is a tremendous honor! Congratulations to our band and Mr. Splettstoeszer.

La Asociación de Educadores de la Música en Connecticut, seleccionaron a la Banda de la Escuela Superior en Torrington, para participar en la Conferencia de la Asociación de Educadores de la Música en Connecticut (Todos los Estados) el Viernes, 12 de Abril del 2019, en el Centro de Convención en Hartford. ¡Este es un gran honor! Felicitaciones a nuestra Banda y al Sr. Splettstoeszer.

post_text:
Good afternoon. This Susan Lubomski, Interim Superintendent for Torrington Public Schools. I am hoping this is my last weather related announcement for this school year! Due to the excessive heat and humidity predicted for Monday, we are scheduling an early release day and cancelling all after school sports activities for tomorrow, Monday, June 18. The TMS Strings concert will still occur on Monday evening in the auditorium. Stay cool!

Buena tardes, Es Susan Lubomski, Superintendente Interino de las Escuelas Públicas de Torrington. text:
Good afternoon. This Susan Lubomski, Interim Superintendent for Torrington Public Schools. I am hoping this is my last weather related announcement for this school year! Due to the excessive heat and humidity predicted for Monday, we are scheduling an early release day and cancelling all after school sports activities for tomorrow, Monday, June 18. The TMS Strings concert will still occur on Monday evening in the auditorium. Stay cool!

Buena tardes, Es Susan Lubomski, Superintendente Interino de las Escuelas Públicas de Torrington. Debido al excesivo calor y humedad previsto para el Lunes, dieciocho de Junio, habra salida temprana mañana y cancelaremos todas las actividades de deportes después de la escuela. El concierto de Cuerdas de la TMS se realizara el Lunes por la noche en el auditorio. ¡Mantenerse fresco!
